<html t:type="layout" title="Grid Enhancements"
	xmlns:t="http://tapestry.apache.org/schema/tapestry_5_1_0.xsd" xmlns:p="tapestry:parameter">

	<p>
		Two grid enhancements are provided as mixins to the grid component:
		<ul>
			<li>
				<strong>GridColumnSort:</strong>
				Persists the sorting column in the URL.
			</li>
			<li>
				<strong>GridColumnSort:</strong>
				Persists the current grid page in the URL.
			</li>
		</ul>
		The two mixins don't change any existing code.
	</p>

	<p>However an additional functionality is provided solving the
		following problem: when one of the miixins is used in a page, clicking
		an action (or page) link to the same page loses the URL parameter. To
		solve tihs issue a utility annotation is provided
		@KeepRequestParameters which when used on a page, decorates all
		component event links and page render links in that page, adding all the parameters
		in the request to links.</p>

	<div style="float:left">
		<t:grid t:id="g1" source="employees100" t:mixins="gridColumnSort, gridCurrentPage"
			rowsPerPage="10" />
	</div>

	<div style="float:left; margin-left: 20px;">
		<t:grid t:id="g2" source="employees100" t:mixins="gridColumnSort, gridCurrentPage"
			rowsPerPage="5" />
	</div>

</html>
